,"code":"-1"},{"type":"text","text":" then the source is never woken up on the basis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the passage of time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dispatching the source does not reset the ready time.  You should do","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"so yourself, from the source dispatch function.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that if you have a pair of sources where the ready time of one","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"suggests that it will be delivered first but the priority for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"other suggests that it would be delivered first, and the ready time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for both sources is reached during the same main context iteration,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then the order of dispatch is undefined."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is a no-op to call this function on a [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true},{"text":"] which has","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"already been destroyed with [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.destroy"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This API is only intended to be used by implementations of [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Do not call this API on a [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] that you did not create."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source"